I would like to believe that I genuinely value the Libre Software principles, ethics, and the whole ecosystem around it. And on the other hand, I do not like nor agree with the business and ethical practices of these huge corporate companies.
But with certain choices, there come certain sacrifices as well. The term &lsquo;sacrifices&rsquo; here can be put to debate but, you get the point&hellip;
So, as an undergraduate student Bacheloring in Computer Engineering, I am displayed with several job offerings from fortune 500 tech companies, several &ldquo;open source&rdquo; projects, some campaigns, and other community/developer advocacy programs that would require me to speak something pleasant about their products and services in exchange of possible recognition or compensation in the form of swags, money or other resources&hellip;
